  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building resilient rural communities in West Africa by supporting inclusive and sustainable local production of Shea butter</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Shea butter local industry has been identified as an agro-food processing industry with high growth potential which could further improve the quality and efficiency of the traditional production methods, directly contributing to local communities# empowerment and economic resilience. Several West African countries have informally requested UNIDO to support the Shea traditional industry in the ECOWAS region including Mali, Guinea, Burkina Faso, Liberia, among others. Moreover, a letter of intent has been received from the Netherlands Development Organisation (SNV), to further collaborate with UNIDO in the advancement of Shea butter sector. Building on the success of previous UNIDO and SNV joint interventions in the beer brewing and meat grilling sectors in Burkina Faso, UNIDO and SNV decided to scale up their partnership to the regional level through a project aiming at transforming traditional Shea butter production into a modern, income generating, and environmentally friendly industry that contributes to poverty eradication and job creation.</narrative>
  </description>
